wiki.content: The song starts off with an angry grunt that plays on loop. "I was in the studio, and for some reason, I couldn't hit a particular note," Lloyd explained to MTV News regarding the guttural noise. "I get really frustrated with myself when I can't do something, so I made the 'ugh' sound, and they kept it in." (Source Want U Back Songfacts) User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License and may also be available under the GNU FDL.
